                <h1>Understanding FedRAMP: A Key to Cloud Security</h1>
                <p>FedRAMP (Federal Risk and Authorization Management Program) is a U.S. government initiative designed to standardize security assessments for cloud products and services. It ensures that cloud solutions used by federal agencies meet stringent security requirements, thereby promoting efficiency and safeguarding sensitive government data.</p>
